title: High profile women stand out on the 2024 Rock & Roll Hall of Fame shortlist
description: Mariah Carey, Cher, Sinéad O'Connor, Mary J. Blige and Sade are on the latest inductee shortlist. It's notable for an institution long focused on white male artists.

title: Israel says it discovered tunnels under U.N. agency's Gaza headquarters
description: The Israeli military said it discovered a network of tunnels under the UNRWA headquarters in Gaza City. UNRWA said it did not know what was underneath its headquarters.

title: Super Bowl 2024: How to watch the Chiefs v. 49ers
description: The Kansas City Chiefs will play the San Francisco 49ers in Las Vegas for Super Bowl 58 on Sunday. Here's what you need to know going into the big game.

title: Cheap, plentiful and devastating: The synthetic drug kush is walloping Sierra Leone
description: Kush, a synthetic cannabinoid, is spreading quickly for the promise of a stress-relieving high. But what's the impact on users — and Sierra Leonean society? And how are the authorities responding?

title: We asked. You answered. Here are your secrets to healthy aging
description: NPR asked our audiences to share their hard-won wisdom. We heard from more than 1,000 people, aged 16 to 103! Here's a roundup of your best advice for thriving as you age.

title: Some say the Las Vegas Super Bowl is rigged. And not because of Taylor Swift
description: When Allegiant Stadium in Las Vegas was built, a worker said he buried a Chiefs Kingdom flag in the field. Kansas City has never lost a game there, sparking a controversial conspiracy theory.

title: Biden's rough week highlights his biggest vulnerability — one he can't change
description: President Biden's most glaring vulnerability in his reelection campaign is his age, and it was front and center this week in a special counsel report about his handling of classified documents.

title: Special counsel's report on classified documents has echoes of the 2016 election
description: For people who were involved with Hillary Clinton's failed 2016 presidential campaign, the echoes of then-FBI Director James Comey's press conference on July 5, 2016, are hard to miss.

title: Republicans see Latino voters in Nevada as key to retaking the White House in 2024
description: Former President Donald Trump has pretty sharp rhetoric around immigration. At the same time, he is trying to reach a potentially powerful voting bloc in pivtal swing states: Latinos.

title: Vets' jewelry company feels the 'Swift effect' after the singer wore diamond bracelet
description: A year ago NPR talked with two former U.S. Army Rangers who started a jewelry company. After Taylor Swift wore one of their bracelets at a football game, their sales jumped 2,000%.

title: Former Maryland Gov. Larry Hogan is running for the U.S. Senate
description: The move gives Republicans a prominent candidate who is well-positioned to run a competitive campaign for the GOP in a state that hasn't had a Republican U.S. senator in 37 years.

title: Hawaii's high court cites 'The Wire' in its ruling on gun rights
description: It says a man can be prosecuted for carrying a gun in public without a permit citing "The Wire" and invokes the "spirit of Aloha" in  rebuke of a U.S. Supreme Court decision that expanded gun rights.
